---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms & Conditions"
  description="RevAudio terms and conditions — purchases, refunds, warranty, licensing, and support policy."
>
  <section class="plugin-detail">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 760px;">
      <h1>Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated: 2026-06-10</p>

      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        RevAudio (&ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;) builds and sells audio software plugins through this website,
        revaudio.net. By purchasing or using our products, or by using this site, you agree to these terms.
        If you do not agree, please do not use the site or the products.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Products</h2>
      <p>
        Our products are digital software (VST3 audio plugins for Windows; macOS support where stated on the
        product page). System requirements, supported hosts, and current limitations are listed on each product
        page &mdash; please check them before buying. Demo versions, where available, are the recommended way to
        verify compatibility with your setup.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Ordering &amp; payment</h2>
      <p>
        Purchases are processed by our payment provider, which acts as the merchant of record. Your payment
        details are handled entirely by the provider &mdash; we never see or store card numbers. Prices are shown
        at checkout including any applicable taxes (VAT/GST), which are determined by your billing location.
        Promotional prices apply only during the stated promotion window.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Delivery</h2>
      <p>
        Products are delivered digitally. After successful payment you receive a download link and licence
        details by email, normally within minutes. Nothing is shipped physically. If your order email does not
        arrive within one hour, check your spam folder, then contact
        <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a> and we will re-send it.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Refunds</h2>
      <p>
        We offer a <strong>14-day money-back guarantee</strong> on all purchases. If a plugin doesn't work for
        you &mdash; technically or creatively &mdash; email
        <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a> within 14 days of purchase and we will
        refund you in full. We may ask what went wrong so we can improve, but a refund inside the window never
        depends on the answer. After a refund, your licence is revoked and you must remove the software from
        your machines. Refunds are issued to the original payment method by our payment provider; bank
        processing can take a few business days.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Licensing</h2>
      <p>
        Plugins are licensed, not sold. Your purchase grants a personal licence as described in the
        <a href="/eula">End-User Licence Agreement</a> &mdash; in short: one user, your own machines,
        perpetual use, free updates within the same major version. The EULA is part of these terms.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Support &amp; updates</h2>
      <p>
        We provide email support for current products at
        <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a>. We aim to respond within two business
        days. Bug-fix updates within your licensed major version are free. We support the current major version
        and, for critical fixes, the one before it. Operating-system and host (DAW) compatibility targets are
        stated per product and may evolve as platforms change.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Warranty</h2>
      <p>
        Beyond the 14-day guarantee above, products are provided <em>&ldquo;as is&rdquo;</em>. We test and
        measure every release, but audio software runs across countless host, driver, and hardware combinations
        and we cannot warrant uninterrupted or error-free operation on every system. Nothing in these terms
        limits statutory consumer rights that apply in your country &mdash; where local consumer law grants you
        stronger rights, those rights prevail.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, our total liability for any claim related to a product or this
        site is limited to the amount you paid for the product concerned. We are not liable for indirect or
        consequential damages &mdash; including lost profits, lost projects, lost audio data, or studio downtime.
        Always keep backups of your sessions.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Acceptable use of this site</h2>
      <p>
        You may not attempt to disrupt the site, scrape it at scale, probe or bypass its security, or use it to
        distribute unlawful content. Product pages, artwork, sound demos, and brand assets are our intellectual
        property and may not be reused commercially without written permission.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        We collect the minimum needed to run the store and we do not sell personal data. What we collect, why,
        how long we keep it, and your rights are set out in full in our
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>. To have your data deleted, email
        <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms as the product line and the law evolve. The version published on this page at
        the time of your purchase applies to that purchase. Material changes will be dated at the top of this
        page.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Israel, without affecting any mandatory consumer
        protections of your country of residence. Disputes will first be addressed in good faith by email
        &mdash; most things are fixable with a conversation.
      </p>

      <h2>14. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Legal questions: <a href="mailto:info@revaudio.net">info@revaudio.net</a><br />
        Everything else: <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
